The '''Lagos State Civil Service''' consists of employees in Lagos State government agencies other than the military.<Ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vanguardngr.com/2014/08/lagos-absorbs-880-kai-officials-civil-service/|title=Lagos absorbs 880 KAI officials into civil service|work=Vanguard News}}</ref> Most employees under the service are career civil servants in the Lagos state ministries, progressing based on qualifications and seniority.<Ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pmnewsnigeria.com/2013/10/12/williams-succeeds-ogunlewe-as-lagos-head-of-service/|title=Williams succeeds Ogunlewe as Lagos Head of service - P.M. NEWS Nigeria|work=pmnewsnigeria.com}}</ref> The civil service is held by [[Lagos State Head of Service|Head of Service]], a senior member of the state civil service appointed by the state Governor.<Ref>{{cite web|url=http://thenewsnigeria.com.ng/2015/02/16/lagos-names-another-female-head-of-service/|title=Lagos names another female head of service|work=The NEWS}}</ref>
==Organization== The civil service is mainly organized around the state ministries, headed by a commissioner appointed by the Governor of Lagos state.<Ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theworldfolio.com/news/olusola-oworu-commissioner-lagos-state-ministry-commerce-and-industry-nigeria-n1216/1216/|title=Nigeria - Honorable Commissioner for the Lagos State Ministry of Commerce and Industry, Mrs. Olusola|author=The Worldfolio|date=11 June 2012|work=theworldfolio.com}}</ref> The Governor's appointments are confirmed by the State House of Representatives.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thisdaylive.com/articles/lagos-cabinet-fashola-submits-37-names-to-assembly/93964/|title=Lagos Cabinet: Fashola Submits 37 Names to Assembly , Articles - THISDAY LIVE|work=thisdaylive.com|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150416183314/http://www.thisdaylive.com/articles/lagos-cabinet-fashola-submits-37-names-to-assembly/93964/|archivedate=2015-04-16|df=}}</ref> There are 24 [[List of government ministries of Lagos State|government ministries of Lagos State]].<Ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vanguardngr.com/2011/07/fashola-swears-in-commissioners/|title=Fashola swears-in commissioners|work=Vanguard News}}</ref> In some cases a commissioner is responsible for more than one ministry, for example Ministry of Establishments, Training and Pensions may be combined as [[Lagos State Ministry of Establishments, Training and Pensions]] and the commissioners are assisted by a Permanent Secretary, who is a senior civil servant.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://newtelegraphonline.com/lagos-developers-seal-deals-new-waterfront-estates/|title=New Telegraph – Lagos, developers seal deals on new waterfront estates|author=Our Correspondent|work=newtelegraphonline.com|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402134556/http://newtelegraphonline.com/lagos-developers-seal-deals-new-waterfront-estates/|archivedate=2015-04-02|df=}}</ref> The ministries are responsible for various parastatals(government-owned corporations) such as universities (Education) and the State Broadcasting Commission.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thisdaylive.com/articles/lagos-restates-commitment-to-rural-development/193300/|title=Lagos Restates Commitment to Rural Development, Articles - THISDAY LIVE|work=thisdaylive.com|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402170212/http://www.thisdaylive.com/articles/lagos-restates-commitment-to-rural-development/193300/|archivedate=2015-04-02|df=}}</ref> The Lagos state ministry is coordinated by the Commissioner, assisted by a Permanent Secretary, who head the civil service departments.<Ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vanguardngr.com/2011/05/lagos-set-to-unveil-new-waterfront-schemes/|title=Lagos set to unveil new waterfront schemes|work=Vanguard News}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vanguardngr.com/2015/02/nysc-takes-health-initiative-to-rural-dwellers/|title=NYSC takes health initiative to rural dwellers|work=Vanguard News}}</ref>
